remove rows (data) from a table
Table structure stays (only data is removed)

Example table (before)

student_id	name	age	city
1	Ravi	20	Chennai
2	Kumar	21	Madurai
3	Anu	19	Coimbatore

1️⃣ Delete one row
DELETE FROM students
WHERE student_id = 2;

Result
1 row deleted

After delete
| 1 | Ravi | 20 | Chennai |
| 3 | Anu  | 19 | Coimbatore |

2️⃣ Delete multiple rows
DELETE FROM students
WHERE age < 20;

Result
1 row deleted

After delete
| 1 | Ravi | 20 | Chennai |
| 2 | Kumar | 21 | Madurai |

3️⃣ Delete all rows
DELETE FROM students;
⚠️ Result
All rows deleted

After delete
Empty table (0 rows)

❗ Important rule

Always use WHERE

DELETE FROM students WHERE student_id = 1;  -- safe
DELETE FROM students;                       -- dangerous ⚠️

Simple understanding
DELETE with WHERE → remove selected rows
DELETE without WHERE → remove everything

One-line memory trick

DELETE = remove data (carefully!)


1️⃣ Check before delete
SELECT * FROM students WHERE age < 20;
2️⃣ Use transaction (safe)
START TRANSACTION;

DELETE FROM students WHERE student_id = 2;

ROLLBACK;  -- undo if mistake
